	<item>
		<title>Getting Started with PHP 8.2</title>
		<link>https://example.com/2025/01/getting-started-with-php-82/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 15 Jan 2025 10:30:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=10</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>PHP 8.2 brings exciting new features to the language. In this post, we'll explore the most important changes.</p>

<h2>Readonly Classes</h2>
<p>One of the headline features is readonly classes, which make all properties readonly by default.</p>

<pre><code>readonly class User {
    public function __construct(
        public string $name,
        public string $email,
    ) {}
}</code></pre>

<h2>Disjunctive Normal Form Types</h2>
<p>DNF types allow combining union and intersection types for more expressive type declarations.</p>

<p>Stay tuned for more PHP tips and tutorials!</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[PHP 8.2 brings exciting new features including readonly classes and DNF types. Let's explore what's new.]]></excerpt:encoded>
