	<item>
		<title>Building REST APIs with Slim 4</title>
		<link>https://example.com/2025/03/building-rest-apis-with-slim-4/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 03 Mar 2025 14:15:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[janewriter]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=30</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Slim 4 is a powerful micro-framework perfect for building RESTful APIs. Let's walk through creating a complete API.</p>

<h2>Setting Up</h2>
<p>Start by installing Slim via Composer:</p>
<pre><code>composer require slim/slim slim/psr7</code></pre>

<h2>Defining Routes</h2>
<p>Slim's routing is clean and intuitive:</p>
<pre><code>$app->get('/api/users', ListUsersAction::class);
$app->post('/api/users', CreateUserAction::class);
$app->get('/api/users/{id}', GetUserAction::class);</code></pre>

<h2>Middleware</h2>
<p>Add authentication, CORS, and other cross-cutting concerns with middleware.</p>

<p>In the next post, we'll add database integration and testing.</p>]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[A hands-on guide to building REST APIs using the Slim 4 PHP micro-framework.]]></excerpt:encoded>
